# Enhanced Lesson Management System

## Unified Interface Pattern

The lesson management interface provides all functionality from a single screen without requiring navigation to separate pages.

**File**: [src/components/admin/LessonManagement.tsx](mdc:src/components/admin/LessonManagement.tsx)

## Key Features

### Dashboard Statistics
Shows at-a-glance metrics at the top:
```typescript
const stats = {
  totalLessons: lessons.length,
  totalVideos: lessons.reduce((sum, l) => sum + (l.videos?.length || 0), 0),
  published: lessons.filter(l => l.published).length,
  draft: lessons.filter(l => !l.published).length,
  unitCount: new Set(lessons.map(l => l.unit)).size
}
```

Display pattern:
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-4 mt-3">
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
    <BookOpen className="h-4 w-4 text-blue-600" />
    <span className="font-semibold">{stats.totalLessons}</span>
    <span className="text-gray-600">Lessons</span>
  </div>
  {/* More stats... */}
</div>
```

### Enhanced Lesson Cards

Each lesson card displays:
- **Expandable/Collapsible** - Click chevron to toggle details
- **Status Badges** - Published/Draft with icons
- **Quick Stats Row**:
  - Video count with icon
  - Objectives count
  - Estimated time
  - Content status indicator

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-4 mt-3 text-sm">
  <div className="flex items-center gap-1.5">
    <Video className="h-4 w-4 text-purple-600" />
    <span className="font-medium">{lesson.videos?.length || 0}</span>
    <span className="text-gray-600">videos</span>
  </div>
  {/* More stats... */}
</div>
```

### Inline Actions
All actions available without leaving the page:
- **Video Icon (purple)** - Opens inline video manager
- **Eye Icon (blue)** - Preview as student (new tab)
- **Edit Icon (gray)** - Edit lesson details
- **Trash Icon (red)** - Delete lesson

### Expandable Details
When expanded, lesson cards show:
- **Metadata** - Slug, created/updated dates
- **Learning Objectives** - Full list with numbering
- **Videos** - List with play links to YouTube

### Inline Video Management
Clicking the video icon reveals LessonVideoManager directly in the card:
```tsx
{isManagingVideos && (
  <CardContent className="pt-4 border-t bg-purple-50/30">
    <LessonVideoManager
      lessonId={lesson.id}
      lessonTitle={lesson.title}
      initialVideos={lesson.videos || []}
      onSave={(videos) => handleVideoSave(lesson.id, videos)}
    />
  </CardContent>
)}
```

## State Management Pattern

```typescript
const [expandedLesson, setExpandedLesson] = useState<string | null>(null)
const [managingVideos, setManagingVideos] = useState<string | null>(null)

const toggleExpand = (lessonId: string) => {
  setExpandedLesson(prev => prev === lessonId ? null : lessonId)
}

const isExpanded = expandedLesson === lesson.id
const isManagingVideos = managingVideos === lesson.id
```

